PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1776704798
OL,3,C'He was sat there in the wardrobe':
OL,4,CWoman tells of stalking experience
OL,6,F"And then also fear of if I put them
OL,7,Fin the bin and he turns up and sees
OL,8,Fthat I have chucked them. Is that
OL,9,Fgoing to be a repercussion for me?"
OL,11,FHannah started slowly trying to cut
OL,12,Foff social media communication with
OL,13,Fher ex-partner before blocking him
OL,14,Fentirely to enjoy a night out with
OL,15,Ffriends.
OL,17,FThat evening Hannah stayed at a
OL,18,Ffriend's house before waking to
OL,19,Fdiscover her stalker had gone into
OL,20,F"meltdown" realising he couldn't
OL,21,Fcontact her.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@cO]|D@AOU|D@JO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/15
