OL,3,C'He was sat there in the wardrobe':
OL,4,CWoman tells of stalking experience
OL,6,FReturning home later in the day with
OL,7,Fher friend, the pair did a sweep of
OL,8,Fthe house to check it was safe for
OL,9,FHannah to return.
OL,11,FHer friend then left, but as Hannah
OL,12,Fwent to lock the door she recalled:
OL,13,F"The plastic frame from around the
OL,14,Fwindow popped out towards me, which I
OL,15,Fwas like well, that's not a thing that
OL,16,Fusually happens?"
OL,18,FAs she went to call her friend back,
OL,19,Fthe window fell through entirely,
OL,20,Fsmashing onto the floor.
OL,26,@uD@AOUxD@QO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/15
