OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1776704798
OL,3,C'He was sat there in the wardrobe':
OL,4,CWoman tells of stalking experience
OL,6,FAt the same moment Hannah realised a
OL,7,Fkey that was always left on the inside
OL,8,Fof a side door had vanished which
OL,9,Finstantly rang alarm bells.
OL,11,FShe said: "At that point, that's when
OL,12,FI was like, he's in this house. I know
OL,13,Fhe's here.
OL,15,F"I think I was just sliding along
OL,16,Ffloors and looking under beds with
OL,17,Fhim, whipping back the shower curtain,
OL,18,Fopened up every door I could.
OL,26,@sD@KOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/15
